comment.narrative:
1. An online advocacy campaign on the rights of PWDs was conducted using the advocacy and outreach materials and advocacy recommendations developed in accessible formats for PWDs and included 12 - radio programme sessions; 1 leaflet; 1 one pager; 1 infographic; 4 accessible video and animations; 5 press-releases; 4 success stories.

Available statistics on PWDs in Uzbekistan was collected and structured in consistent order to be used for advocacy materials.

2.1.1. Sets of technical equipment were provided to the Republican Inspection of Medical and Social Expertise and the Association of Disabled People of Uzbekistan to ensure that DPOs enhance the capacity in the application and introduction of the principles and norms of UNCRPD and ICF.
2.1.2 Functions and activities of DPOs in Uzbekistan were studied and analysed. Information on DPOs activities and their contacts was collected in order to further partnership and collaboration with them in the form of database.
2.1.3 The project signed Memorandum of Understanding with the Association of Disabled People of Uzbekistan on partnership and further collaboration in the field of the protection of rights and interests of persons with disabilities. The Association has 27 member DPOs across the country;

2.2.1 An overview analysis was conducted and recommendations were developed on the accessibility and affordability of public services, including technical, medical and social services for PwDs in Uzbekistan; 
2.2.2 The access of women with disabilities to employment opportunities, in particular in the context of COVID-19 related restrictive measures was analysed; 

3 Advocacy campaign on the ICF and CRPD norms, SDG and on the rights of persons with disabilities were regularly conducted among DPOs in partnership with the Association of DPOs.
Series of radio programs specifically dedicated to the rights and interests of people with disabilities were prepared and broadcast; accessible video materials and easy-to-read leaflets were widely shared among the disability community
